<br />
yeah, I know smarty, it's irritating for those of us that don't abuse the system. But the alternative is simply making a fairly difficult to enforce rule to which the result of breaking it would be banning/deleting/in some way punishing those people. It also serves as a keep-people-alive longer thing. The old cooldown was vastly different than this would be. 10 minutes for both attacker and the defender, defender could not be sieged for another 10 minutes, attacker could not siege for another 10 minutes. Death was exceedingly rare.
<br />

<br />
DT brought up an alternative solution that I didn't entirely understand that would break the scripts more or less I think.</td>	</tr></table><span class="postbody">
<br />

<br />
If I recall correctly too Cyph, the rape cooldown occured across the board (ie you get a planet raped off you, and NO ONE could rape you for 10 mins...that was pretty gay)...a small cooldown to prevent the script from really being effective would be good, and i am no sure i would have the across the board cooldown, or if the cooldown should just be for the attacker<br />_________________<br />Houston
