			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">would it be possible to simply let protection kick in after a player lost 1/3 of their planets, rather than 2/3? and then allow total war to take the rest but have a cooldown for sieging planets after a player is in protection.
<br />

<br />
ie player A has 30 planets, gets total war declared upon by player B. Player B takes the first ten planets within a minute, and needs to wait for 20 seconds after sieging each consecutive player, since player A is in protection?
<br />

<br />
That way core-building would still be easily possible, and players are better protected from rape-scripts or killing. I know this is a bit of a compromise solution, since people could technically still use rape scripts etc for the first third of planets but it is slightly less gay than having to wait for ages to be able to siege even through someone's cover and thus keeps some of the speed of sieging? And doing the actual killing would then become a bit of a pain.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
